{
  "stem": "17761.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 110.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "He came in the morning with a general, a German general , who freed all the Jews and gave the order to the Romanian army and to the-- to those [NON-ENGLISH] to leave the place.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And that was it for that time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And I think it-- I am happy to mention the name of Nathan Klipper, who did a lot of good things to our community [? especially. ?] [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] OK.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "By the way, these [NON-ENGLISH], they also killed-- they assassinated the Romanian prime minister, who was quite a democrat-- he was the name of Armand Calinescu, A-R-M-A-N-D, Calinescu, C-A-L-I-N-E-S-C-U-- about two days before Yom Kippur.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But at that time, the-- the Romania army reacted so strongly that they executed thousands of [NON-ENGLISH] in a few days.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the general who did it, his name was [NON-ENGLISH] and we used to call him [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Except for these, not.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Perhaps one thing that-- but that was after I left Arbore.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The goyim wanted to-- to-- that the Jews should leave this little place, so they used to throw in into their houses-- we called it bombs, but they were-- they were hand grenades to explode.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The damage was more than physical casualties.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But this really caused that the Jews in many, many of those villages left to the cities.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My own family was not anymore there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We went earlier to the Bessarabia, to Sculen.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But my grandfather, he came over-- he sent over first his son Shimon.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he opened up a business in Vatra-Dornei.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then he came over to Vatra-Dornei and lived in Vatra-Dornei.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not as far as I can remember.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, in Arbore.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But in Vatra-Dornei, there were some people who came from other places.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
